# Manual Verification Only

- Make the requested source or documentation changes, but do not run build, test, lint, type-check, formatting, simulation, deployment, or other verification commands.
- Do not start development servers, runtime processes, simulators, or watchers to validate changes.
- Do not use IDE diagnostics as a verification step after editing.
- The user will manually perform all build and verification work.
- In the final response, clearly state that verification was not run according to this project rule.
